{\an1}H-Honey?

25:36.743 --> 25:38.787
(Mike exhales)

25:38.870 --> 25:43.708
{\an1}MIKE: Oh, it felt good
letting that guy have it.

25:44.918 --> 25:46.962
Yeah?

25:44.918 --> 25:46.962
{\an1}Yeah.

25:47.045 --> 25:50.257
{\an1}MIKE:
It felt real good.

26:02.227 --> 26:04.437
{\an1}Ah...

26:07.732 --> 26:09.651
We forgot your birthday cake.

26:09.734 --> 26:12.821
{\an1}All right.

26:12.904 --> 26:16.992
♪ Happy birthday to you ♪

26:17.075 --> 26:19.869
♪ Happy birthday ♪

26:19.953 --> 26:22.998
♪ To you ♪

26:23.081 --> 26:27.961
♪ Happy birthday, dear Martha ♪

26:28.044 --> 26:31.381
♪ Happy birthday ♪

26:31.464 --> 26:33.883
♪ To you. ♪

26:35.969 --> 26:37.345
{\an1}Honey,

26:37.429 --> 26:38.805
blow out the candles.

26:38.888 --> 26:40.682
But don't forget to make a wish.

26:40.765 --> 26:42.934
(trembling gasp)

26:43.018 --> 26:46.354
Do it! Please.

26:46.438 --> 26:48.565
I-I don't,
I don't want to, Mike.

26:48.648 --> 26:50.567
Do it!

26:55.155 --> 26:57.699
(sharp exhale)

26:57.782 --> 26:59.826
{\an1}Oh, you got
to come closer.

27:14.632 --> 27:17.677
Yay!

27:17.761 --> 27:21.931
Hey, maybe we should wait
until Cole gets home.

27:22.015 --> 27:23.558
{\an5}Cole...

27:22.015 --> 27:23.558
{\an3}Huh, Mike?

27:23.641 --> 27:26.061
{\an3}Just, uh, put it down,
and-and wait...

27:26.144 --> 27:27.687
You know...

27:27.771 --> 27:30.357
(laughs)
I just saved you two

27:30.440 --> 27:31.733
from a fucking psychopath.

27:31.816 --> 27:34.903
{\an1}How about
a little thank you?

27:34.986 --> 27:36.488
Okay, Mike, you-you-you,
you don't have to yell.

27:36.571 --> 27:39.616
I'm not yelling!

27:41.659 --> 27:44.079
{\an1}You know,
maybe next time,

27:44.162 --> 27:47.248
you don't lead
a lunatic to my house.

27:47.332 --> 27:50.377
Two girls drinking
at a fucking bar?

27:50.460 --> 27:52.003
You're asking for it.

27:52.087 --> 27:55.131
{\an5}A-Asking for it?

27:52.087 --> 27:55.131
Don't interrupt me!

27:55.215 --> 27:57.801
I am done with you
interrupting me!

27:57.884 --> 28:00.136
Every time I have
a fucking story,

28:00.220 --> 28:02.222
you got to open
that mouth of yours!

28:02.305 --> 28:05.767
{\an1}I'm trying
to keep you safe!

28:05.850 --> 28:10.480
{\an3}Uh... Mike?

28:10.563 --> 28:14.567
{\an3}Hey, uh, I need you
to listen to me.

28:14.651 --> 28:17.946
I have to explain something
about you.

28:18.029 --> 28:19.948
Is this what you wanted?

28:20.031 --> 28:22.117
Did you want him
to follow you home?

28:22.200 --> 28:23.785
{\an5}Of course not.

28:22.200 --> 28:23.785
Shut up, Annie!

28:23.868 --> 28:25.453
I'm talking to my wife!

28:25.537 --> 28:26.788
{\an5}(screams)

28:25.537 --> 28:26.788
(glass shatters)

28:26.871 --> 28:28.164
Wait, Mike! What happened? Mike!

28:28.248 --> 28:30.250
{\an3}Mike! Mike!

28:30.333 --> 28:32.335
Stop it! No...

28:34.712 --> 28:36.714
(grunts)

28:42.887 --> 28:45.598
(panting)

28:45.682 --> 28:49.269
Uh, Martha?

28:49.352 --> 28:50.854
{\an5}(whispering):
We need to leave.

28:49.352 --> 28:50.854
{\an3}(moaning)

28:50.937 --> 28:53.773
{\an5}We need to leave right now.

28:50.937 --> 28:53.773
{\an3}C-Cole.

28:53.857 --> 28:56.609
{\an4}We-- we've-- we have
to get Cole. He went out.

28:53.857 --> 28:56.609
{\an3}Uh...

28:56.693 --> 28:58.528
He's with Steve at the docks.

28:58.611 --> 29:00.613
{\an5}We have to go.

28:58.611 --> 29:00.613
{\an3}Okay.

29:04.659 --> 29:06.202
(gasps)

29:06.286 --> 29:07.454
What?! Oh...

29:07.537 --> 29:08.663
Oh, oh, God.

29:08.746 --> 29:10.665
(Martha moaning)

29:10.748 --> 29:12.667
(engine starts)

29:14.419 --> 29:16.379
MARTHA:
<i>C-Cole didn't touch a meteor.</i>

29:16.463 --> 29:17.964
A-Annie, he'll be safe, right?

29:18.047 --> 29:19.841
{\an5}I'm sure he's okay,
I'm sure he's okay.

29:18.047 --> 29:19.841
You promise?

29:19.924 --> 29:22.844
(tires screeching)

29:22.927 --> 29:25.763
(moaning, grunting)

29:25.847 --> 29:27.265
{\an5}(siren wailing)

29:25.847 --> 29:27.265
{\an1}Annie?

29:27.348 --> 29:29.142
{\an1}I'm okay.

29:29.225 --> 29:30.685
{\an1}Fuck...
(clears throat)

29:30.768 --> 29:35.023
Oh, my God.
Oh, my God.

29:35.106 --> 29:37.317
{\an1}Ow...

29:37.400 --> 29:40.069
{\an1}Oh...

29:40.153 --> 29:42.530
Annie? What are you...?

29:42.614 --> 29:44.365
Oh, God.

29:44.449 --> 29:46.451
(panting)

29:50.580 --> 29:52.499
(dog barking in distance)

29:52.582 --> 29:54.667
(helicopter whirring)

29:54.751 --> 29:57.170
Oh, my God.

30:00.131 --> 30:01.716
{\an1}(gasps)

30:01.799 --> 30:03.343
Annie...

30:03.426 --> 30:05.428
(footsteps approaching)

30:09.807 --> 30:12.519
(panting)

30:12.602 --> 30:14.187
Oh, my God.

30:20.109 --> 30:22.070
We have to go.

30:22.153 --> 30:24.822
{\an1}We have...
We have to get Cole.

30:25.949 --> 30:28.076
We gotta get Cole.

30:28.159 --> 30:29.661
MAN (in distance):
Let's kill 'em all!

30:35.500 --> 30:39.420
Uh, the docks should just be...
a few blocks that way.

30:39.504 --> 30:41.464
(both scream)

30:41.548 --> 30:43.216
Crazy night, huh?

30:44.634 --> 30:45.718
(grunting)

30:49.514 --> 30:50.557
(screams)

30:50.640 --> 30:52.684
(shouting)

30:58.189 --> 30:59.107
{\an3}Hey, Annie!

30:59.190 --> 31:01.150
{\an5}Don't you remember me?

30:59.190 --> 31:01.150
{\an1}(screams)

31:09.200 --> 31:10.618
(screams)

31:18.042 --> 31:19.961
Get him out!

31:20.044 --> 31:21.462
Get the fuck out of the car!

31:21.546 --> 31:24.132
(grunting and shouting)

31:27.719 --> 31:30.430
{\an5}PHIL:
Annie! Wait! Please!

31:27.719 --> 31:30.430
{\an3}Is it Phil?

31:30.513 --> 31:32.807
Annie! Listen to me.

31:32.890 --> 31:34.642
I don't have it. Okay?

31:34.726 --> 31:37.145
It's not all us men, okay?

31:37.228 --> 31:38.396
It can't be all of us.

31:38.479 --> 31:40.148
{\an3}It did seem likely to me
that it's probably

31:40.231 --> 31:42.358
a, uh, hormonal reaction,

31:42.442 --> 31:44.485
{\an3}but that would mean that-that
it's also highly likely

31:44.569 --> 31:46.696
that it's a chromosomal
interaction with the Y...

31:46.779 --> 31:47.822
{\an6}(voice distorts):
chromosome...

31:46.779 --> 31:47.822
Hold up!

31:47.905 --> 31:49.198
Hey, look, it's unlikely

31:49.282 --> 31:51.451
that the mineral itself
is the culprit here!

31:51.534 --> 31:52.493
{\an3}I'm sorry!

31:52.577 --> 31:55.330
(growling)

31:55.413 --> 31:57.290
(both screaming)

32:02.378 --> 32:05.214
{\an3}Oh...
Come on, come on.

32:05.298 --> 32:07.508
{\an3}Oh... oh...
oh, my God.

32:07.592 --> 32:08.801
What is happening?

32:08.885 --> 32:12.680
{\an1}This is, this is crazy!
(exhales)

32:12.764 --> 32:15.725
{\an3}Annie, we have
to do something.

32:15.808 --> 32:17.685
{\an3}Um...

32:24.567 --> 32:26.027
What are you doing?

32:26.110 --> 32:30.365
{\an3}These... these things
are making them stronger.

32:30.448 --> 32:31.658
{\an3}We...

32:31.741 --> 32:33.534
we have to try.

32:33.618 --> 32:35.662
{\an3}Okay?

32:35.745 --> 32:36.913
We have to fight back.

32:52.095 --> 32:53.846
{\an3}Aw, fuck!

32:53.930 --> 32:55.014
It's not doing anything!

32:55.098 --> 32:58.476
Martha... Martha, you know why.

33:01.270 --> 33:04.065
It's just the men.

33:05.775 --> 33:07.568
{\an5}Get off my property!

33:05.775 --> 33:07.568
(both scream)

33:15.410 --> 33:17.203
What the fuck?

33:17.286 --> 33:19.747
(opera music playing)

33:19.831 --> 33:21.666
(shouting)

33:30.758 --> 33:32.385
Fuck you, Chad!

33:32.468 --> 33:34.762
Fuck you, Becky!

33:34.846 --> 33:38.057
Fuck your feelings! (screams)

33:40.810 --> 33:44.021
(opera music continues playing)

33:50.278 --> 33:53.990
(grunting)

33:54.073 --> 33:58.202
{\an5}Amazing, right? (chuckles)

33:54.073 --> 33:58.202
Um, mm-hmm.

34:00.329 --> 34:01.372
Whew.

34:07.086 --> 34:08.337
{\an3}Ooh!

34:08.420 --> 34:10.172
(laughs) Come on.

34:10.255 --> 34:11.299
I'm telling you, baby.

34:13.760 --> 34:15.969
{\an3}It changes you.
Makes you stronger.

34:16.053 --> 34:18.473
Um... no, I'm-I'm...

34:18.556 --> 34:20.641
{\an1}I actually don't really
want to drink that.

34:20.725 --> 34:21.641
{\an3}Why not?

34:21.726 --> 34:23.728
{\an3}Come on.

34:28.608 --> 34:31.610
{\an5}What's wrong?

34:28.608 --> 34:31.610
Um... nothing.

34:31.694 --> 34:32.987
{\an1}I'm just...
not in the mood.

34:33.070 --> 34:36.282
Come on.
Don't be such a prude.

34:39.076 --> 34:41.286
{\an1}Hey.

34:39.076 --> 34:41.286
What's your problem?

34:41.370 --> 34:42.538
{\an1}I, uh...

34:41.370 --> 34:42.538
You're okay?

34:42.621 --> 34:44.540
Yeah, I... I am,

34:44.623 --> 34:46.417
{\an1}I just don't want to do this
right now, okay?

34:50.087 --> 34:51.839
S-Steve...

34:51.922 --> 34:54.967
{\an1}S-Steve?

34:55.051 --> 34:56.427
Hey.

34:56.511 --> 34:59.180
{\an3}They're on a boat
called the <i> Achilles.</i>

34:59.263 --> 35:01.599
{\an5}How do you know that?

34:59.263 --> 35:01.599
Ah, don't ask.

35:03.142 --> 35:04.519
{\an3}MARTHA:
Cole, please.

35:04.602 --> 35:06.521
{\an5}(Steve grunting)

35:04.602 --> 35:06.521
{\an3}Cole?

35:06.604 --> 35:08.314
(grunting)
Come on!

35:09.941 --> 35:12.401
{\an3}Cole? Cole!
Cole! Honey...

35:12.485 --> 35:14.320
{\an4}STEVE:
Come on!

35:12.485 --> 35:14.320
Are you okay?

35:14.403 --> 35:16.364
{\an6}Look at me.
Are you okay?

35:14.403 --> 35:16.364
Yeah, just... it-it was...

35:16.447 --> 35:19.033
{\an6}(grunting)

35:16.447 --> 35:19.033
{\an1}Steve, he just, he just
went crazy. I don't--

35:19.116 --> 35:21.285
{\an5}I don't know what I did...

35:19.116 --> 35:21.285
{\an3}You didn't do anything, honey,
it's not your fault.

35:21.369 --> 35:22.912
{\an3}It's-- It's
the meteorites.

35:22.995 --> 35:25.706
(panting)
I swear he's a good guy.

35:25.790 --> 35:28.042
He was just obsessed
with that stupid fucking rock.

35:28.125 --> 35:31.712
{\an3}DYLAN:
♪ I've been alone ♪

35:31.796 --> 35:35.258
{\an5}(chain rattling)

35:31.796 --> 35:35.258
♪ Without you in my life ♪

35:39.637 --> 35:43.057
♪ And in my dreams ♪

35:43.140 --> 35:44.892
♪ I've kissed your lips ♪

35:44.976 --> 35:49.313
♪ A thousand times ♪

35:52.316 --> 35:54.152
{\an3}♪ Hello ♪

35:56.320 --> 35:59.740
♪ Is it me you're looking for? ♪

36:02.994 --> 36:04.996
It was magic, Annie.

36:05.079 --> 36:07.248
It was cosmic.

36:14.672 --> 36:17.466
Why don't you like me?

36:23.181 --> 36:25.057
{\an3}(quietly):
What the fuck is that?

36:36.319 --> 36:39.614
(whispering):
Annie.

36:39.697 --> 36:41.157
{\an5}(growling):
Annie!

36:39.697 --> 36:41.157
(screaming)

36:41.240 --> 36:42.742
{\an5}No! No!

36:41.240 --> 36:42.742
(screaming)

36:42.825 --> 36:44.410
(Dylan grunting)

36:48.039 --> 36:49.123
(grunts)

36:51.375 --> 36:52.960
No, no, no, no;
no, no, no, no!

36:53.044 --> 36:55.755
(grunts)

36:57.840 --> 37:00.301
{\an3}Cole, look at me!
Cole, please, baby...

37:00.384 --> 37:02.428
{\an3}(grunting)

37:02.511 --> 37:04.305
(helicopter whirring)

37:31.707 --> 37:33.834
{\an5}Hey!

37:31.707 --> 37:33.834
{\an1}Cole!

37:35.419 --> 37:37.004
{\an3}Cole!

37:37.088 --> 37:40.508
{\an4}(panting)

37:37.088 --> 37:40.508
Okay. It's okay, baby.

37:43.386 --> 37:44.637
Hey!

37:44.720 --> 37:46.722
{\an3}Hey!

38:01.904 --> 38:03.906
(indistinct radio chatter)

38:06.367 --> 38:08.202
No organic compounds
in this one.

38:08.286 --> 38:11.664
{\an5}No parasites. No bacteria.

38:08.286 --> 38:11.664
Then it must be chemical.

38:11.747 --> 38:12.999
{\an3}The meteors.
The water.

38:13.082 --> 38:15.418
{\an3}It's the only commonality
amongst these men.

38:15.501 --> 38:16.502
Something caused this.

38:16.585 --> 38:18.713
Hi.

38:16.585 --> 38:18.713
{\an1}I, uh--

38:18.796 --> 38:20.172
They took my blood.

38:20.256 --> 38:22.258
{\an3}Yeah.

38:20.256 --> 38:22.258
I'm cool, I guess.

38:22.341 --> 38:24.885
{\an1}MARTHA:
Okay. (exhales)

38:24.969 --> 38:26.846
{\an1}COLE: But I had this
in my back pocket

38:26.929 --> 38:28.681
the whole night, so...

38:28.764 --> 38:30.891
What? But Cole, Steve was near
that, and it happened to him.

38:30.975 --> 38:33.602
{\an1}Yeah.
That's what I'm saying.

38:33.686 --> 38:35.938
It's not all of us.

38:36.022 --> 38:37.523
Maybe there is no cure.

38:37.606 --> 38:39.191
She's right.

38:39.275 --> 38:41.068
Honey, don't say that.
Dad's gonna be fine.

38:41.152 --> 38:42.903
They're not gonna find anything.

38:42.987 --> 38:44.447
Because there's no disease.

38:44.530 --> 38:45.948
The meteors, they...

38:46.032 --> 38:47.783
{\an5}they were a placebo.

38:46.032 --> 38:47.783
There's no cure because

38:47.867 --> 38:49.618
it'll always be inside me.

38:49.702 --> 38:50.786
What?

38:50.870 --> 38:52.038
I...

38:52.121 --> 38:53.748
{\an3}ANNIE: You stopped
yourself from turning.

38:53.831 --> 38:55.541
I saw you.

38:55.624 --> 38:57.585
That's the thing.

38:57.668 --> 39:01.422
I chose to.

39:01.505 --> 39:02.965
I just chose to.

39:12.183 --> 39:14.477
{\an5}IDs, please.

39:12.183 --> 39:14.477
Oh, um...

39:14.560 --> 39:16.145
{\an1}Okay.

39:22.485 --> 39:25.738
You know, I bet you'd look
much cuter if you smiled.

39:25.821 --> 39:27.073
What did you say?

39:27.156 --> 39:29.158
{\an1}SOLDIER: Why don't you
try it sometime?

39:32.536 --> 39:34.538
No.

39:40.669 --> 39:42.171
{\an5}NEWS ANCHOR:
When we come back,
a mass shooting

39:42.254 --> 39:43.756
claims the lives of 13.

39:43.839 --> 39:45.257
{\an5}The suspect
was a man in his 20s

39:45.341 --> 39:47.468
with no motive yet known.

39:47.551 --> 39:50.137
{\an5}And two men are in custody
after a road rage incident.

39:50.221 --> 39:51.639
More after this.

39:53.766 --> 39:56.811
{\an3}Tonight, Annie Miller found
herself in the center

39:56.894 --> 39:59.647
of a mysterious
and violent epidemic.

39:59.730 --> 40:01.941
What she encountered
was no material disease,

40:02.024 --> 40:04.485
but rather a plague
of conscience.

40:04.568 --> 40:07.154
One that gave men
permission to ignore decency,

40:07.238 --> 40:08.781
consent and fear.

40:08.864 --> 40:11.033
And tonight, all it took

40:11.117 --> 40:16.622
was a few innocuous little rocks
to turn men into monsters.

40:16.705 --> 40:20.417
Here... in The Twilight Zone.
